c\x8dk-fa-s\xe1\xb9\xb3</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Taiwanese_Language_Phonetic_Alphabet" title="Taiwanese Language Phonetic Alphabet">TLPA</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th style="padding:0.1em;background:#ccc"><a href="/wiki/Gan_Chinese" title="Gan Chinese">Gan</a></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0 0.1em 0.4em">\n<div class="NavFrame collapsed" style="border:none;padding:0">\n<div class="NavHead" style="font-size:105%;background:transparent;text-align:left"><a href="/wiki/Chang-Du_dialect" title="Chang-Du dialect">Chang-Du dialect</a></div>\n<div class="NavContent" style="font-size:105%;padding:0.2em 0 0.4em;text-align:center;text-align:left">\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Pha%CC%8Dk-oa-chhi_romanization" title="Pha\xcc\x8dk-oa-chhi romanization">Pha\xcc\x8dk-oa-chhi</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th style="padding:0.1em;background:#ccc">See also</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0 0.1em 0.4em">\n<div class="NavFrame collapsed" style="border:none;padding:0">\n<div class="NavHead" style="font-size:105%;background:transparent;text-align:left">Other transliterations</div>\n<div class="NavContent" style="font-size:105%;padding:0.2em 0 0.4em;text-align:center;text-align:left">\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/General_Chinese" title="General Chinese">General Chinese</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Cyrillization_of_Chinese" title="Cyrillization of Chinese">Cyrillization</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Xiao%27erjing" title="Xiao\'erjing">Xiao\'erjing</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/%27Phags-pa_script" title="\'Phags-pa script">\'Phags-pa script</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Bopomofo" title="Bopomofo">Bopomofo</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Taiwanese_kana" title="Taiwanese kana">Taiwanese kana</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Taiwanese_Phonetic_Symbols" title="Taiwanese Phonetic Symbols">Taiwanese Phonetic Symbols</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Mongolian_transliteration_of_Chinese_characters" title="Mongolian transliteration of Chinese characters">Mongolian transliteration of Chinese characters</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Manchu_alphabet#History" title="Manchu alphabet">Manchu transliteration</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Transcription_into_Chinese_characters" title="Transcription into Chinese characters">Transcription into Chinese</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="padding:0 0.1em 0.4em">\n<div class="NavFrame collapsed" style="border:none;padding:0">\n<div class="NavHead" style="font-size:105%;background:transparent;text-align:left">By place</div>\n<div class="NavContent" style="font-size:105%;padding:0.2em 0 0.4em;text-align:center;text-align:left">\n<ul>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Hong_Kong_name" title="Hong Kong name">Romanization in Hong Kong</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Chinese_language_romanisation_in_Singapore" title="Chinese language romanisation in Singapore">Romanization in Singapore</a></li>\n<li><a href="/wiki/Chinese_language_romanization_in_Taiwan" title="Chinese language romanization in Taiwan">Romanization in Taiwan</a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style="text-align:right;font-size:115%;padding-top: 0.6em;">\n<div class="plainlinks hlist navbar mini">\n<ul>\n<li class="nv-view"><a href="/wiki/Template:RCL" title="Template:RCL"><abbr title="View this template">v</abbr></a></li>\n<li class="nv-talk"><a href="/wiki/Template_talk:RCL" title="Template talk:RCL"><abbr title="Discuss this template">t</abbr></a></li>\n<li class="nv-edit"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:RCL&amp;action=edit"><abbr title="Edit this template">e</abbr></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><b>Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles</b> (<span class="nowrap"><span class="IPA nopopups noexcerpt"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA/English" title="Help:IPA/English">/<span style="border-bottom:1px dotted"><span title="/\xcb\x8c/: secondary stress follows">\xcb\x8c</span><span title="\'w\' in \'wind\'">w</span><span title="/e\xc9\xaa/: \'a\' in \'face\'">e\xc9\xaa</span><span title="\'d\' in \'dye\'">d</span></span> <span style="border-bottom:1px dotted"><span title="/\xcb\x88/: primary stress follows">\xcb\x88</span><span title="/d\xca\x92/: \'j\' in \'jam\'">d\xca\x92</span><span title="/a\xc9\xaa/: \'i\' in \'tide\'">a\xc9\xaa</span><span title="\'l\' in \'lie\'">l</span><span title="\'z\' in \'zoom\'">z</span></span>/</a></span></span>), sometimes abbreviated <b>Wade</b>,<sup class="noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2016)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup> is a <a href="/wiki/Romanization_of_Chinese" title="Romanization of Chinese">Romanization</a> system for <a href="/wiki/Standard_Chinese" title="Standard Chinese">Mandarin Chinese</a>. It developed from a system produced by <a href="/wiki/Thomas_Francis_Wade" title="Thomas Francis Wade">Thomas Wade</a>, during the mid-19th century, and was given completed form with <a href="/wiki/Herbert_Giles" title="Herbert Giles">Herbert A. Giles</a>\'s <i><a href="/wiki/A_Chinese-English_Dictionary" title="A Chinese-English Dictionary">Chinese\xe2\x80\x93English Dictionary</a></i> of 1892.</p>\n<p>Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles was the system of transcription in the English-speaking world for most of the 20th century, used in standard reference books and in English language books published before 1979. It replaced the <a href="/wiki/Nanking_dialect" class="mw-redirect" title="Nanking dialect">Nanking dialect</a>-based romanization systems that had been common until the late 19th century, such as the <a href="/wiki/Postal_Romanization" class="mw-redirect" title="Postal Romanization">Postal Romanization</a> (still used in some place-names). In <a href="/wiki/PRC" class="mw-redirect" title="PRC">mainland China</a> it has been entirely replaced by the <a href="/wiki/Hanyu_Pinyin" class="mw-redirect" title="Hanyu Pinyin">Hanyu Pinyin</a> system approved in 1958. Outside mainland China, it has mostly been replaced by P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn, even though <a href="/wiki/Taiwan" title="Taiwan">Taiwan</a> implements a multitude of Romanization systems in daily life. Additionally, its usage can be seen in the common English names of certain individuals and locations such as <a href="/wiki/Chiang_Ching-kuo" title="Chiang Ching-kuo">Chiang Ching-kuo</a>.</p>\n<p></p>\n<div id="toc" class="toc">\n<div class="toctitle">\n<h2>Contents</h2>\n</div>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-1"><a href="#History"><span class="tocnumber">1</span> <span class="toctext">History</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-2"><a href="#Initials_and_finals"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Initials and finals</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-3"><a href="#Initials"><span class="tocnumber">2.1</span> <span class="toctext">Initials</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-4"><a href="#Finals"><span class="tocnumber">2.2</span> <span class="toctext">Finals</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-5"><a href="#Syllables_that_begin_with_a_medial"><span class="tocnumber">2.3</span> <span class="toctext">Syllables that begin with a medial</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-6"><a href="#System_features"><span class="tocnumber">3</span> <span class="toctext">System features</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-7"><a href="#Consonants_and_initial_symbols"><span class="tocnumber">3.1</span> <span class="toctext">Consonants and initial symbols</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-8"><a href="#Vowels_and_final_symbols"><span class="tocnumber">3.2</span> <span class="toctext">Vowels and final symbols</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-3 tocsection-9"><a href="#Syllabic_consonants"><span class="tocnumber">3.2.1</span> <span class="toctext">Syllabic consonants</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-3 tocsection-10"><a href="#Vowel_o"><span class="tocnumber">3.2.2</span> <span class="toctext">Vowel o</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-11"><a href="#Tones"><span class="tocnumber">3.3</span> <span class="toctext">Tones</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-12"><a href="#Punctuation"><span class="tocnumber">3.4</span> <span class="toctext">Punctuation</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-13"><a href="#Comparison_with_other_systems"><span class="tocnumber">4</span> <span class="toctext">Comparison with other systems</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-14"><a href="#P.C4.ABny.C4.ABn"><span class="tocnumber">4.1</span> <span class="toctext">P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-15"><a href="#Chart"><span class="tocnumber">4.2</span> <span class="toctext">Chart</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-16"><a href="#Intuitiveness_issues"><span class="tocnumber">5</span> <span class="toctext">Intuitiveness issues</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-17"><a href="#Adaptations"><span class="tocnumber">6</span> <span class="toctext">Adaptations</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-18"><a href="#Mathews"><span class="tocnumber">6.1</span> <span class="toctext"><i>Mathews</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-19"><a href="#See_also"><span class="tocnumber">7</span> <span class="toctext">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-20"><a href="#References"><span class="tocnumber">8</span> <span class="toctext">References</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-21"><a href="#External_links"><span class="tocnumber">9</span> <span class="toctext">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<p></p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="History">History</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wade%E2%80%93Giles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: History">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles was developed by <a href="/wiki/Thomas_Francis_Wade" title="Thomas Francis Wade">Thomas Francis Wade</a>, a scholar of Chinese and a British ambassador in China who was the first professor of Chinese at <a href="/wiki/Cambridge_University" class="mw-redirect" title="Cambridge University">Cambridge University</a>. Wade published in 1867 the first textbook on the <a href="/wiki/Beijing_dialect" title="Beijing dialect">Beijing dialect</a> of <a href="/wiki/Mandarin_Chinese" title="Mandarin Chinese">Mandarin</a> in English, <i>Y\xc3\xbc-yen Tz\xc5\xad-erh Chi</i> (traditional: <span lang="zh-Hant" xml:lang="zh-Hant">\xe8\xaa\x9e\xe8\xa8\x80\xe8\x87\xaa\xe9\x82\x87\xe9\x9b\x86</span>; simplified: \xe8\xaf\xad\xe8\xa8\x80\xe8\x87\xaa\xe8\xbf\xa9\xe9\x9b\x86),<sup id="cite_ref-Kaske2008_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Kaske2008-1">[1]</a></sup> which became the basis for the Romanization system later known as Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles. The system, designed to transcribe Chinese terms for Chinese specialists, was further refined in 1912 by <a href="/wiki/Herbert_Allen_Giles" class="mw-redirect" title="Herbert Allen Giles">Herbert Allen Giles</a>, a British diplomat in China and his son, <a href="/wiki/Lionel_Giles" title="Lionel Giles">Lionel Giles</a>,<sup class="noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources. (September 2016)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup> a curator at the British Museum.<sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2">[2]</a></sup></p>\n<p><a href="/wiki/Taiwan" title="Taiwan">Taiwan</a> has used Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles for decades as the <i><a href="/wiki/De_facto" title="De facto">de facto</a></i> standard, co-existing with several official but obscure <a href="/wiki/Romanization" title="Romanization">Romanizations</a> in succession, namely, <a href="/wiki/Gwoyeu_Romatzyh" title="Gwoyeu Romatzyh">Gwoyeu Romatzyh</a> (1928), <a href="/wiki/Mandarin_Phonetic_Symbols_II" title="Mandarin Phonetic Symbols II">Mandarin Phonetic Symbols II</a> (1986), and <a href="/wiki/Tongyong_Pinyin" title="Tongyong Pinyin">Tongyong Pinyin</a> (2000). With the election of the <a href="/wiki/Kuomintang" title="Kuomintang">Kuomintang</a> party in Taiwan in 2008, Taiwan officially switched to <a href="/wiki/Hanyu_Pinyin" class="mw-redirect" title="Hanyu Pinyin">Hanyu Pinyin</a>. However, many people in Taiwan, both native and overseas, use or transcribe their legal names in the Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles system, as well as the other aforementioned systems.</p>\n<p><a href="/wiki/Singapore" title="Singapore">Singapore</a> has also made limited use of Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles romanization,<sup class="noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style="white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title="Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title="This claim needs references to reliable sources. (November 2016)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup> such as in the romanization of the middle syllable of <a href="/wiki/Lee_Hsien_Loong" title="Lee Hsien Loong">Lee Hsien Loong</a>\'s name.</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Initials_and_finals">Initials and finals</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wade%E2%80%93Giles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2" title="Edit section: Initials and finals">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The tables below show the Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles representation of each <a href="/wiki/Standard_Chinese_phonology" title="Standard Chinese phonology">Chinese sound</a> (in bold type),<sup id="cite_ref-3" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-3">[3]</a></sup> together with the corresponding <a href="/wiki/IPA" class="mw-redirect" title="IPA">IPA</a> phonetic symbol (in square brackets), and equivalent representations in <a href="/wiki/B%C5%8Dp%C5%8Dm%C5%8Df%C5%8D" class="mw-redirect" title="B\xc5\x8dp\xc5\x8dm\xc5\x8df\xc5\x8d">Zh\xc3\xb9y\xc4\xabn F\xc3\xbah\xc3\xa0o (B\xc5\x8dp\xc5\x8dm\xc5\x8df\xc5\x8d)</a> and <a href="/wiki/H%C3%A0ny%C7%94_P%C4%ABny%C4%ABn" class="mw-redirect" title="H\xc3\xa0ny\xc7\x94 P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn">H\xc3\xa0ny\xc7\x94 P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn</a>.</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Initials">Initials</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wade%E2%80%93Giles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3" title="Edit section: Initials">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<table class="wikitable" style="text-align:center;">\n<tr>\n<th rowspan="2" colspan="2"></th>\n<th colspan="2"><a href="/wiki/Bilabial_consonant" title="Bilabial consonant">Bilabial</a></th>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Labiodental_consonant" title="Labiodental consonant">Labiodental</a></th>\n<th colspan="2"><a href="/wiki/Dental_consonant" title="Dental consonant">Dental</a>/<a href="/wiki/Alveolar_consonant" title="Alveolar consonant">Alveolar</a></th>\n<th colspan="2"><a href="/wiki/Retroflex_consonant" title="Retroflex consonant">Retroflex</a></th>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Alveolo-palatal_consonant" title="Alveolo-palatal consonant">Alveolo-palatal</a></th>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Velar_consonant" title="Velar consonant">Velar</a></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Voicelessness" title="Voicelessness">Voiceless</a></th>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Voice_(phonetics)" title="Voice (phonetics)">Voiced</a></th>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Voicelessness" title="Voicelessness">Voiceless</a></th>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Voicelessness" title="Voicelessness">Voiceless</a></th>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Voice_(phonetics)" title="Voice (phonetics)">Voiced</a></th>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Voicelessness" title="Voicelessness">Voiceless</a></th>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Voice_(phonetics)" title="Voice (phonetics)">Voiced</a></th>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Voicelessness" title="Voicelessness">Voiceless</a></th>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Voicelessness" title="Voicelessness">Voiceless</a></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan="2"><a href="/wiki/Nasal_consonant" title="Nasal consonant">Nasal</a></th>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Bilabial_nasal" title="Bilabial nasal"><b><big>m</big></b> [m]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x87 m</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Alveolar_nasal" class="mw-redirect" title="Alveolar nasal"><b><big>n</big></b> [n]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x8b n</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th rowspan="2"><a href="/wiki/Plosive" class="mw-redirect" title="Plosive">Plosive</a></th>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Aspirated_consonant" title="Aspirated consonant">Unaspirated</a></th>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_bilabial_plosive" class="mw-redirect" title="Voiceless bilabial plosive"><b><big>p</big></b> [p]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x85 b</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_alveolar_plosive" class="mw-redirect" title="Voiceless alveolar plosive"><b><big>t</big></b> [t]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x89 d</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_velar_plosive" class="mw-redirect" title="Voiceless velar plosive"><b><big>k</big></b> [k]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x8d g</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Aspirated_consonant" title="Aspirated consonant">Aspirated</a></th>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_bilabial_plosive" class="mw-redirect" title="Voiceless bilabial plosive"><b><big>p\xca\xbb</big></b> [p\xca\xb0]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x86 p</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_alveolar_plosive" class="mw-redirect" title="Voiceless alveolar plosive"><b><big>t\xca\xbb</big></b> [t\xca\xb0]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x8a t</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_velar_plosive" class="mw-redirect" title="Voiceless velar plosive"><b><big>k\xca\xbb</big></b> [k\xca\xb0]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x8e k</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th rowspan="2"><a href="/wiki/Affricate_consonant" title="Affricate consonant">Affricate</a></th>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Aspirated_consonant" title="Aspirated consonant">Unaspirated</a></th>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_alveolar_affricate" title="Voiceless alveolar affricate"><b><big>ts</big></b> [ts]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x97 z</td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_retroflex_affricate" title="Voiceless retroflex affricate"><b><big>ch</big></b> [\xca\x88\xca\x82]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x93 zh</td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_alveolo-palatal_affricate" title="Voiceless alveolo-palatal affricate"><b><big>ch</big></b> [t\xc9\x95]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x90 j</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th><a href="/wiki/Aspirated_consonant" title="Aspirated consonant">Aspirated</a></th>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_alveolar_affricate" title="Voiceless alveolar affricate"><b><big>ts\xca\xbb</big></b> [ts\xca\xb0]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x98 c</td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_retroflex_affricate" title="Voiceless retroflex affricate"><b><big>ch\xca\xbb</big></b> [\xca\x88\xca\x82\xca\xb0]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x94 ch</td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_alveolo-palatal_affricate" title="Voiceless alveolo-palatal affricate"><b><big>ch\xca\xbb</big></b> [t\xc9\x95\xca\xb0]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x91 q</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan="2"><a href="/wiki/Fricative_consonant" title="Fricative consonant">Fricative</a></th>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_labiodental_fricative" title="Voiceless labiodental fricative"><b><big>f</big></b> [f]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x88 f</td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_alveolar_sibilant" class="mw-redirect" title="Voiceless alveolar sibilant"><b><big>s</big></b> [s]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x99 s</td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_retroflex_sibilant" title="Voiceless retroflex sibilant"><b><big>sh</big></b> [\xca\x82]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x95 sh</td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_alveolo-palatal_sibilant" title="Voiceless alveolo-palatal sibilant"><b><big>hs</big></b> [\xc9\x95]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x92 x</td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Voiceless_velar_fricative" title="Voiceless velar fricative"><b><big>h</big></b> [x]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x8f h</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan="2"><a href="/wiki/Liquid_consonant" title="Liquid consonant">Liquid</a></th>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Alveolar_lateral_approximant" class="mw-redirect" title="Alveolar lateral approximant"><b><big>l</big></b> [l]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x8c l</td>\n<td></td>\n<td><a href="/wiki/Retroflex_approximant" title="Retroflex approximant"><b><big>j</big></b> [\xc9\xbb~\xca\x90]</a><br />\n\xe3\x84\x96 r</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>Instead of <i>ts</i>, <i>ts\xca\xbb</i> and <i>s</i>, Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles writes <i>tz</i>, <i>tz\xca\xbb</i> and <i>ss</i> before <i>\xc5\xad</i> (see <a href="/wiki/Wade%E2%80%93Giles#Syllabic_consonants" title="Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles">below</a>).</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Finals">Finals</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wade%E2%80%93Giles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Finals">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<table class="wikitable" style="text-align:center;">\n<tr>\n<th colspan="2" rowspan="2"></th>\n<th colspan="13">Coda</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan="3">\xe2\x88\x85</th>\n<th colspan="2"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/i/</span></th>\n<th colspan="2"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/u/</span></th>\n<th colspan="2"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/n/</span></th>\n<th colspan="3"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/\xc5\x8b/</span></th>\n<th><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/\xc9\xbb/</span></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th rowspan="4">Medial</th>\n<th>\xe2\x88\x85</th>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>ih/\xc5\xad</big></b><br />\n[\xc9\xa8]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xad<a href="/wiki/File:U%2B312D.svg" class="image"><img alt="U+312D.svg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/U%2B312D.svg/15px-U%2B312D.svg.png" width="15" height="15" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/U%2B312D.svg/23px-U%2B312D.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7b/U%2B312D.svg/30px-U%2B312D.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="72" data-file-height="72" /></a> -i</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>\xc3\xaa/o</big></b><br />\n[\xc9\xa4]<br />\n\xe3\x84\x9c e</td>\n<td><b><big>a</big></b><br />\n[a]<br />\n\xe3\x84\x9a a</td>\n<td><b><big>ei</big></b><br />\n[ei]<br />\n\xe3\x84\x9f ei</td>\n<td><b><big>ai</big></b><br />\n[ai]<br />\n\xe3\x84\x9e ai</td>\n<td><b><big>ou</big></b><br />\n[ou]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa1 ou</td>\n<td><b><big>ao</big></b><br />\n[au]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa0 ao</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>\xc3\xaan</big></b><br />\n[\xc9\x99n]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa3 en</td>\n<td><b><big>an</big></b><br />\n[an]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa2 an</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>ung</big></b><br />\n[\xca\x8a\xc5\x8b]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\xa5 ong</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>\xc3\xaang</big></b><br />\n[\xc9\x99\xc5\x8b]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa5 eng</td>\n<td><b><big>ang</big></b><br />\n[a\xc5\x8b]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa4 ang</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>\xc3\xaarh</big></b><br />\n[a\xc9\x9a\xcc\xaf]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa6 er</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/j/</span></th>\n<td><b><big>i</big></b><br />\n[i]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7 i</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>ieh</big></b><br />\n[je]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\x9d ie</td>\n<td><b><big>ia</big></b><br />\n[ja]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\x9a ia</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td><b><big>iu</big></b><br />\n[jou]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\xa1 iu</td>\n<td><b><big>iao</big></b><br />\n[jau]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\xa0 iao</td>\n<td><b><big>in</big></b><br />\n[in]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\xa3 in</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>ien</big></b><br />\n[j\xc9\x9bn]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\xa2 ian</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>iung</big></b><br />\n[j\xca\x8a\xc5\x8b]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa9\xe3\x84\xa5 iong</td>\n<td><b><big>ing</big></b><br />\n[i\xc5\x8b]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\xa5 ing</td>\n<td><b><big>iang</big></b><br />\n[ja\xc5\x8b]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\xa4 iang</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/w/</span></th>\n<td><b><big>u</big></b><br />\n[u]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8 u</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>o/uo</big></b><br />\n[wo]<br />\n\xe3\x84\x9b/\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9b o/uo</td>\n<td><b><big>ua</big></b><br />\n[wa]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9a ua</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>ui/uei</big></b><br />\n[wei]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9f ui</td>\n<td><b><big>uai</big></b><br />\n[wai]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9e uai</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td><b><big>un</big></b><br />\n[w\xc9\x99n]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\xa3 un</td>\n<td><b><big>uan</big></b><br />\n[wan]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\xa2 uan</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td><b><big>uang</big></b><br />\n[wa\xc5\x8b]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\xa4 uang</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/\xc9\xa5/</span></th>\n<td><b><big>\xc3\xbc</big></b><br />\n[y]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa9 \xc3\xbc</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>\xc3\xbceh</big></b><br />\n[\xc9\xa5e]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa9\xe3\x84\x9d \xc3\xbce</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td><b><big>\xc3\xbcn</big></b><br />\n[yn]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa9\xe3\x84\xa3 \xc3\xbcn</td>\n<td><b><big>\xc3\xbcan</big></b><br />\n[\xc9\xa5\xc9\x9bn]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa9\xe3\x84\xa2 \xc3\xbcan</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles writes <i>-uei</i> after <i>k\xca\xbb</i> and <i>k</i>, otherwise <i>-ui</i>: <i>k\xca\xbbuei</i>, <i>kuei</i>, <i>hui</i>, <i>shui</i>, <i>ch\xca\xbbui</i>.</p>\n<p>It writes <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[-\xc9\xa4]</span> as <i>-o</i> after <i>k\xca\xbb</i>, <i>k</i> and <i>h</i>, otherwise <i>-\xc3\xaa</i>: <i>k\xca\xbbo</i>, <i>ko</i>, <i>ho</i>, <i>sh\xc3\xaa</i>, <i>ch\xca\xbb\xc3\xaa</i>. When <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[\xc9\xa4]</span> forms a syllable on its own, it is written <i>\xc3\xaa</i> or <i>o</i> depending on the character.</p>\n<p>Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles writes <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[-wo]</span> as <i>-uo</i> after <i>k\xca\xbb</i>, <i>k</i>, <i>h</i> and <i>sh</i>, otherwise <i>-o</i>: <i>k\xca\xbbuo</i>, <i>kuo</i>, <i>huo</i>, <i>shuo</i>, <i>ch\xca\xbbo</i>.</p>\n<p>For <i>-ih</i> and <i>-\xc5\xad</i>, see <a href="/wiki/Wade%E2%80%93Giles#Syllabic_consonants" title="Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles">below</a>.</p>\n<p>Giles\'s <i><a href="/wiki/A_Chinese-English_Dictionary" title="A Chinese-English Dictionary">A Chinese-English Dictionary</a></i> also includes the syllables <i>chio</i>, <i>ch\xca\xbbio</i>, <i>hsio</i>, <i>yo</i>, which are now pronounced like <i>ch\xc3\xbceh</i>, <i>ch\xca\xbb\xc3\xbceh</i>, <i>hs\xc3\xbceh</i>, <i>y\xc3\xbceh</i>.</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Syllables_that_begin_with_a_medial">Syllables that begin with a medial</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wade%E2%80%93Giles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5" title="Edit section: Syllables that begin with a medial">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<table class="wikitable" style="text-align:center;">\n<tr>\n<th colspan="2" rowspan="2"></th>\n<th colspan="13">Coda</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan="3">\xe2\x88\x85</th>\n<th colspan="2"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/i/</span></th>\n<th colspan="2"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/u/</span></th>\n<th colspan="2"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/n/</span></th>\n<th colspan="3"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/\xc5\x8b/</span></th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th rowspan="4">Medial</th>\n<th><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/j/</span></th>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>i/yi</big></b><br />\n[i]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7 yi</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>yeh</big></b><br />\n[je]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\x9d ye</td>\n<td><b><big>ya</big></b><br />\n[ja]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\x9a ya</td>\n<td></td>\n<td><b><big>yai</big></b><br />\n[jai]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\x9e yai</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>yu</big></b><br />\n[jou]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\xa1 you</td>\n<td><b><big>yao</big></b><br />\n[jau]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\xa0 yao</td>\n<td><b><big>yin</big></b><br />\n[in]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\xa3 yin</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>yen</big></b><br />\n[j\xc9\x9bn]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\xa2 yan</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>yung</big></b><br />\n[j\xca\x8a\xc5\x8b]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa9\xe3\x84\xa5 yong</td>\n<td><b><big>ying</big></b><br />\n[i\xc5\x8b]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\xa5 ying</td>\n<td><b><big>yang</big></b><br />\n[ja\xc5\x8b]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa7\xe3\x84\xa4 yang</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/w/</span></th>\n<td><b><big>wu</big></b><br />\n[u]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8 wu</td>\n<td><b><big>wo</big></b><br />\n[wo]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9b wo</td>\n<td><b><big>wa</big></b><br />\n[wa]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9a wa</td>\n<td><b><big>wei</big></b><br />\n[wei]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9f wei</td>\n<td><b><big>wai</big></b><br />\n[wai]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9e wai</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>w\xc3\xaan</big></b><br />\n[w\xc9\x99n]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\xa3 wen</td>\n<td><b><big>wan</big></b><br />\n[wan]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\xa2 wan</td>\n<td></td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>w\xc3\xaang</big></b><br />\n[w\xc9\x99\xc5\x8b]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\xa5 weng</td>\n<td><b><big>wang</big></b><br />\n[wa\xc5\x8b]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\xa4 wang</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/\xc9\xa5/</span></th>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>y\xc3\xbc</big></b><br />\n[y]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa9 yu</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>y\xc3\xbceh</big></b><br />\n[\xc9\xa5e]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa9\xe3\x84\x9d yue</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>y\xc3\xbcn</big></b><br />\n[yn]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa9\xe3\x84\xa3 yun</td>\n<td bgcolor="#EFEFEF"><b><big>y\xc3\xbcan</big></b><br />\n[\xc9\xa5\xc9\x9bn]<br />\n\xe3\x84\xa9\xe3\x84\xa2 yuan</td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles writes the syllable <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[i]</span> as <i>i</i> or <i>yi</i> depending on the character.</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="System_features">System features</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wade%E2%80%93Giles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6" title="Edit section: System features">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Consonants_and_initial_symbols">Consonants and initial symbols</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wade%E2%80%93Giles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7" title="Edit section: Consonants and initial symbols">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>A feature of the Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles system is the representation of the <a href="/wiki/Aspiration_(phonetics)" class="mw-redirect" title="Aspiration (phonetics)">unaspirated-aspirated</a> <a href="/wiki/Stop_consonant" title="Stop consonant">stop consonant</a> pairs using left <a href="/wiki/Apostrophe" title="Apostrophe">apostrophes</a>: <i>p, p\xca\xbb, t, t\xca\xbb, k, k\xca\xbb, ch, ch\xca\xbb</i>. The use of apostrophes preserves <i>b</i>, <i>d</i>, <i>g</i>, and <i>j</i> for the romanization of <a href="/wiki/Varieties_of_Chinese" title="Varieties of Chinese">Chinese varieties</a> containing <a href="/wiki/Voiced" class="mw-redirect" title="Voiced">voiced</a> consonants, such as <a href="/wiki/Shanghainese" title="Shanghainese">Shanghainese</a> (which has a full set of voiced consonants) and <a href="/wiki/Min_Nan" class="mw-redirect" title="Min Nan">Min Nan</a> (H\xc5\x8d-l\xc3\xb3-o\xc4\x93) whose century-old <a href="/wiki/Pe%CC%8Dh-%C5%8De-j%C4%AB" title="Pe\xcc\x8dh-\xc5\x8de-j\xc4\xab">Pe\xcc\x8dh-\xc5\x8de-j\xc4\xab</a> (POJ, often called Missionary Romanization) is similar to Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles. POJ, <a href="/wiki/Legge_romanization" title="Legge romanization">Legge romanization</a>, <a href="/wiki/Simplified_Wade" title="Simplified Wade">Simplified Wade</a>, and <a href="/wiki/EFEO_Chinese_transcription" title="EFEO Chinese transcription">EFEO Chinese transcription</a> use the letter \xe2\x9f\xa8h\xe2\x9f\xa9 instead of an apostrophe to indicate aspiration (this is similar to the superscript <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xca\xb0</span> used in <a href="/wiki/Help:IPA" title="Help:IPA">IPA</a> since the <a href="/wiki/History_of_the_International_Phonetic_Alphabet" title="History of the International Phonetic Alphabet">revisions of the 1970s</a>). The convention of an apostrophe or \xe2\x9f\xa8h\xe2\x9f\xa9 to denote aspiration is also found in romanizations of other Asian languages, such as <a href="/wiki/McCune%E2%80%93Reischauer" title="McCune\xe2\x80\x93Reischauer">McCune\xe2\x80\x93Reischauer</a> for <a href="/wiki/Korean_language" title="Korean language">Korean</a> and <a href="/wiki/ISO_11940" title="ISO 11940">ISO 11940</a> for <a href="/wiki/Thai_language" title="Thai language">Thai</a>.</p>\n<p>People unfamiliar with Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles often ignore the apostrophes, sometimes omitting them when copying texts, unaware that they represent vital information. H\xc3\xa0ny\xc7\x94 P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn addresses this issue by employing the Latin letters customarily used for voiced stops, unneeded in Mandarin, to represent the unaspirated stops: <i>b, p, d, t, g, k, j, q, zh, ch.</i></p>\n<p>Partly because of the popular omission of the apostrophe, the four sounds represented in H\xc3\xa0ny\xc7\x94 P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn by <i>j</i>, <i>q</i>, <i>zh</i>, and <i>ch</i> often all become <i>ch</i>, including in many proper names. However, if the apostrophes are kept, the system reveals a symmetry that leaves no overlap:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The non-<a href="/wiki/Retroflex" class="mw-redirect" title="Retroflex">retroflex</a> <i>ch</i> (P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn <i>j</i>) and <i>ch\xca\xbb</i> (P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn <i>q</i>) are always before either <i>i</i> or <i>\xc3\xbc</i>.</li>\n<li>The <a href="/wiki/Retroflex" class="mw-redirect" title="Retroflex">retroflex</a> <i>ch</i> (P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn <i>zh</i>) and <i>ch\xca\xbb</i> (P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn <i>ch</i>) are always before <i>a</i>, <i>\xc3\xaa</i>, <i>ih</i>, <i>o</i>, or <i>u</i>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Vowels_and_final_symbols">Vowels and final symbols</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wade%E2%80%93Giles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8" title="Edit section: Vowels and final symbols">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Syllabic_consonants">Syllabic consonants</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wade%E2%80%93Giles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Syllabic consonants">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>\n<p>Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles shows precisions not found in other major Romanizations in regard to the rendering of the two types of <a href="/wiki/Syllabic_consonant" title="Syllabic consonant">syllabic consonant</a> (<a href="/wiki/Simplified_Chinese_characters" title="Simplified Chinese characters">simplified Chinese</a>: <span lang="zh-Hans" xml:lang="zh-Hans">\xe7\xa9\xba\xe9\x9f\xb5</span>; <a href="/wiki/Traditional_Chinese_characters" title="Traditional Chinese characters">traditional Chinese</a>: <span lang="zh-Hant" xml:lang="zh-Hant">\xe7\xa9\xba\xe9\x9f\xbb</span>; <a href="/wiki/Pinyin" title="Pinyin">pinyin</a>: <i><span lang="zh-Latn-pinyin" xml:lang="zh-Latn-pinyin">k\xc5\x8dngy\xc3\xb9n</span></i>):</p>\n<ul>\n<li><i>-\xc5\xad</i> after the <a href="/wiki/Sibilant" title="Sibilant">sibilants</a> written in this position (and this position only) as <i>tz</i>, <i>tz\xca\xbb</i> and <i>ss</i> (P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn <i>z</i>, <i>c</i> and <i>s</i>).</li>\n<li><i>-ih</i> after the <a href="/wiki/Retroflex" class="mw-redirect" title="Retroflex">retroflex</a> <i>ch</i>, <i>ch\xca\xbb</i>, <i>sh</i>, and <i>j</i> (P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn <i>zh</i>, <i>ch</i>, <i>sh</i>, and <i>r</i>).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>These finals are both written as <i>-i</i> in <a href="/wiki/H%C3%A0ny%C7%94_P%C4%ABny%C4%ABn" class="mw-redirect" title="H\xc3\xa0ny\xc7\x94 P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn">H\xc3\xa0ny\xc7\x94 P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn</a> (hence distinguishable only by the initial from <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[i]</span> as in <i>li</i>), and as <i>-ih</i> in <a href="/wiki/Tongy%C3%B2ng_Pinyin" class="mw-redirect" title="Tongy\xc3\xb2ng Pinyin">Tongy\xc3\xb2ng Pinyin</a>. They are typically omitted in <a href="/wiki/B%C5%8Dp%C5%8Dm%C5%8Df%C5%8D" class="mw-redirect" title="B\xc5\x8dp\xc5\x8dm\xc5\x8df\xc5\x8d">Zh\xc3\xb9y\xc4\xabn (B\xc5\x8dp\xc5\x8dm\xc5\x8df\xc5\x8d)</a>.</p>\n<table class="wikitable" style="text-align:center;">\n<tr>\n<th colspan="2"><a href="/wiki/International_Phonetic_Alphabet" title="International Phonetic Alphabet">IPA</a></th>\n<td>\xca\x88\xcd\xa1\xca\x82\xc9\xbb\xcc\xa9</td>\n<td>\xca\x88\xcd\xa1\xca\x82\xca\xb0\xc9\xbb\xcc\xa9</td>\n<td>\xca\x82\xc9\xbb\xcc\xa9</td>\n<td>\xc9\xbb\xc9\xbb\xcc\xa9</td>\n<td>t\xcd\xa1s\xc9\xb9\xcc\xa9</td>\n<td>t\xcd\xa1s\xca\xb0\xc9\xb9\xcc\xa9</td>\n<td>s\xc9\xb9\xcc\xa9</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan="2">Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles</th>\n<td>chih</td>\n<td>ch\xca\xbbih</td>\n<td>shih</td>\n<td>jih</td>\n<td>tz\xc5\xad</td>\n<td>tz\xca\xbb\xc5\xad</td>\n<td>ss\xc5\xad</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan="2"><a href="/wiki/B%C5%8Dp%C5%8Dm%C5%8Df%C5%8D" class="mw-redirect" title="B\xc5\x8dp\xc5\x8dm\xc5\x8df\xc5\x8d">Zh\xc3\xb9y\xc4\xabn</a></th>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x93</td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x94</td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x95</td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x96</td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x97</td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x98</td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x99</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th colspan="2"><a href="/wiki/P%C4%ABny%C4%ABn" class="mw-redirect" title="P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn">P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn</a></th>\n<td>zhi</td>\n<td>chi</td>\n<td>shi</td>\n<td>ri</td>\n<td>zi</td>\n<td>ci</td>\n<td>si</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<h4><span class="mw-headline" id="Vowel_o">Vowel o</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wade%E2%80%93Giles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Vowel o">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h4>\n<p>Final <i>o</i> in Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles has two pronunciations in modern Mandarin: <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[wo]</span> and <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[\xc9\xa4]</span>.</p>\n<p>What is pronounced today as a <a href="/wiki/Close-mid_back_unrounded_vowel" title="Close-mid back unrounded vowel">close-mid back unrounded vowel</a> <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[\xc9\xa4]</span> is written usually as <i>\xc3\xaa</i>, but sometimes as <i>o</i>, depending on historical pronunciation (at the time Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles was developed). Specifically, after velar initials <i>k</i>, <i>k\xca\xbb</i> and <i>h</i> (and a historical <i>ng</i>, which had been dropped by the time Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles was developed), <i>o</i> is used; for example, "\xe5\x93\xa5" is <i>ko<sup>1</sup></i> (P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn <i>g\xc4\x93</i>) and "\xe5\x88\xbb" is <i>k\xca\xbbo<sup>4</sup></i><sup id="cite_ref-4" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-4">[4]</a></sup> (P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn <i>k\xc3\xa8</i>). By modern Mandarin, <i>o</i> after velars (and what used to be <i>ng</i>) have shifted to <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[\xc9\xa4]</span>, thus they are written as <i>ge</i>, <i>ke</i>, <i>he</i> and <i>e</i> in P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn. When <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[\xc9\xa4]</span> forms a syllable on its own, Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles writes <i>\xc3\xaa</i> or <i>o</i> depending on the character. In all other circumstances, it writes <i>\xc3\xaa</i>.</p>\n<p>What is pronounced today as <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[wo]</span> is usually written as <i>o</i> in Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles, except for <i>wo</i>, <i>shuo</i> (e.g. "\xe8\xaa\xaa" <i>shuo<sup>1</sup></i>) and the three syllables of <i>kuo</i>, <i>k\xca\xbbuo</i>, and <i>huo</i> (as in \xe9\x81\x8e, \xe9\x9c\x8d, etc.), which contrast with <i>ko</i>, <i>k\xca\xbbo</i>, and <i>ho</i> that correspond to P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn <i>ge</i>, <i>ke</i>, and <i>he</i>. This is because characters like \xe7\xbe\x85, \xe5\xa4\x9a, etc. (Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles: <i>lo<sup>2</sup></i>, <i>to<sup>1</sup></i>; P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn: <i>lu\xc3\xb3</i>, <i>du\xc5\x8d</i>) did not originally carry the medial <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[w]</span>. By modern Mandarin, the phonemic distinction between <i>o</i> and <i>-uo</i>/<i>wo</i> has been lost (except in interjections when used alone), and the medial <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[w]</span> is added in front of <i>-o</i>, creating the modern <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[wo]</span>.</p>\n<table class="wikitable" style="text-align:center;">\n<tr>\n<th><a href="/wiki/International_Phonetic_Alphabet" title="International Phonetic Alphabet">IPA</a></th>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">pwo</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">p\xca\xb0wo</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">mwo</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">fwo</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">two</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">t\xca\xb0wo</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">nwo</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">lwo</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">k\xc9\xa4</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">k\xca\xb0\xc9\xa4</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">x\xc9\xa4</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xca\x88\xca\x82wo</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xca\x88\xca\x82\xca\xb0wo</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xca\x90wo</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xca\xa6wo</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xca\xa6\xca\xb0wo</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">swo</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc9\xa4</span></td>\n<td><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">wo</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles</th>\n<td>po</td>\n<td>p\xca\xbbo</td>\n<td>mo</td>\n<td>fo</td>\n<td>to</td>\n<td>t\xca\xbbo</td>\n<td>no</td>\n<td>lo</td>\n<td>ko</td>\n<td>k\xca\xbbo</td>\n<td>ho</td>\n<td>cho</td>\n<td>ch\xca\xbbo</td>\n<td>jo</td>\n<td>tso</td>\n<td>ts\xca\xbbo</td>\n<td>so</td>\n<td>o/\xc3\xaa</td>\n<td>wo</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th><a href="/wiki/B%C5%8Dp%C5%8Dm%C5%8Df%C5%8D" class="mw-redirect" title="B\xc5\x8dp\xc5\x8dm\xc5\x8df\xc5\x8d">Zh\xc3\xb9y\xc4\xabn</a></th>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x85<b>\xe3\x84\x9b</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x86<b>\xe3\x84\x9b</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x87<b>\xe3\x84\x9b</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x88<b>\xe3\x84\x9b</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x89<b>\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9b</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x8a<b>\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9b</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x8b<b>\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9b</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x8c<b>\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9b</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x8d<b>\xe3\x84\x9c</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x8e<b>\xe3\x84\x9c</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x8f<b>\xe3\x84\x9c</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x93<b>\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9b</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x94<b>\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9b</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x96<b>\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9b</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x97<b>\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9b</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x98<b>\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9b</b></td>\n<td>\xe3\x84\x99<b>\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9b</b></td>\n<td><b>\xe3\x84\x9c</b></td>\n<td><b>\xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9b</b></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<th><a href="/wiki/P%C4%ABny%C4%ABn" class="mw-redirect" title="P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn">P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn</a></th>\n<td>b<b>o</b></td>\n<td>p<b>o</b></td>\n<td>m<b>o</b></td>\n<td>f<b>o</b></td>\n<td>d<b>uo</b></td>\n<td>t<b>uo</b></td>\n<td>n<b>uo</b></td>\n<td>l<b>uo</b></td>\n<td>g<b>e</b></td>\n<td>k<b>e</b></td>\n<td>h<b>e</b></td>\n<td>zh<b>uo</b></td>\n<td>ch<b>uo</b></td>\n<td>r<b>uo</b></td>\n<td>z<b>uo</b></td>\n<td>c<b>uo</b></td>\n<td>s<b>uo</b></td>\n<td><b>e</b></td>\n<td><b>wo</b></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<p>Note that Zh\xc3\xb9y\xc4\xabn and P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn write <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">[wo]</span> as \xe3\x84\x9b <i>-o</i> after \xe3\x84\x85 <i>b</i>, \xe3\x84\x86 <i>p</i>, \xe3\x84\x87 <i>m</i> and \xe3\x84\x88 <i>f</i>, and as \xe3\x84\xa8\xe3\x84\x9b <i>-uo</i> after all other initials.</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Tones">Tones</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wade%E2%80%93Giles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: Tones">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href="/wiki/Standard_Chinese_phonology#Tones" title="Standard Chinese phonology">Tones</a> are indicated in Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles using superscript numbers (1\xe2\x80\x934) placed after the syllable. This contrasts with the use of diacritics to represent the tones in P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn. For example, the P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn <i>qi\xc3\xa0n</i> (fourth tone) has the Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles equivalent <i>ch\xca\xbbien<sup>4</sup></i>.</p>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Punctuation">Punctuation</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wade%E2%80%93Giles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=12" title="Edit section: Punctuation">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles uses <a href="/wiki/Hyphen" title="Hyphen">hyphens</a> to separate all syllables within a word (whereas P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn separates syllables only in specially defined cases, using hyphens or right apostrophes as appropriate).</p>\n<p>If a syllable is not the first in a word, its first letter is not <a href="/wiki/Majuscule" class="mw-redirect" title="Majuscule">capitalized</a>, even if it is part of a <a href="/wiki/Proper_noun" title="Proper noun">proper noun</a>. The use of apostrophes, hyphens, and capitalization is frequently not observed in place names and personal names. For example, the majority of overseas <a href="/wiki/Taiwanese_people" title="Taiwanese people">Taiwanese</a> write their <a href="/wiki/Given_name" title="Given name">given names</a> like "Tai Lun" or "Tai-Lun", whereas the Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles is actually "Tai-lun". (See also <a href="/wiki/Chinese_name" title="Chinese name">Chinese name</a>.)</p>\n<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Comparison_with_other_systems">Comparison with other systems</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wade%E2%80%93Giles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: Comparison with other systems">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="P.C4.ABny.C4.ABn">P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wade%E2%80%93Giles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles chose the <a href="/wiki/French_language" title="French language">French</a>-like <i>j</i> (implying a sound like IPA\'s [\xca\x92]) to represent a Northern Mandarin pronunciation of what is represented as <i>r</i> in P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn.</li>\n<li><i>\xc3\x9c</i> always has an <a href="/wiki/Diaeresis_(diacritic)" title="Diaeresis (diacritic)">umlaut</a> above, while P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn only employs it in the cases of <i>n\xc3\xbc</i>, <i>l\xc3\xbc</i>, <i>n\xc3\xbce</i> and <i>l\xc3\xbce</i>, while leaving it out after <i>j</i>, <i>q</i>, <i>x</i> and <i>y</i> as a simplification because <i><a href="/wiki/U" title="U">u</a></i> cannot otherwise appear after those letters. Because <i>y\xc3\xbc</i> (as in \xe7\x8e\x89 "jade") must have an umlaut in Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles, the umlaut-less <i>yu</i> in Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles is freed up for what corresponds to <i>you</i> (\xe6\x9c\x89) in Pinyin.</li>\n<li>The P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn cluster <i>-ong</i> is <i>-ung</i> in Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles. (Compare <i><a href="/wiki/Kung_fu" class="mw-redirect" title="Kung fu">kung<sup>1</sup>-fu</a></i> to <i>g\xc5\x8dngfu</i> as an example.)</li>\n<li>After a consonant, both Wade\xe2\x80\x93Giles and P\xc4\xabny\xc4\xabn use <i>-iu</i> and <i>-un</i> instead of the complete syllables: <i>-iou</i> and <i>-u\xc3\xaan</i>/<i>-uen</i>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Chart">Chart</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wade%E2%80%93Giles&amp;action=edit&amp;section=15" title="Edit section: Chart">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>\n<table class="wikitable plainrowheaders">\n<caption>Vowels <i>a, e, o</i></caption>\n<tr>\n<th scope="col"><a href="/wiki/Help:IPA" title="Help:IPA">IPA</a></th>\n<th scope="col"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">a</span></th>\n<th scope="col"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc9\x94</span></th>\n<th scope="col"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc9\x9b</span></th>\n<th scope="col"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc9\xa4</span></th>\n<th scope="col"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">ai</span></th>\n<th scope="col"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">ei</span></th>\n<th scope="col"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">au</span></th>\n<th scope="col"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">ou</span></th>\n<th scope="col"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">an</span></th>\n<th scope="col"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">\xc9\x99n</span></th>\n<th scope="col"><span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">a\xc5\x8b</span></th>\n<th scope="col"><span title="Repr